feat(auth): add x-tablet-id + x-tablet-token authentication support

Extended authContext middleware to support direct tablet authentication using x-tablet-id + x-tablet-token headers (raw token that gets SHA-256 hashed for validation).

Backend now supports THREE authentication methods:
1. User auth: x-user-* headers or Bearer JWT token
2. Tablet JWT auth: x-tablet-session-token (returned by /authenticate endpoint)
3. Tablet raw token auth: x-tablet-id + x-tablet-token (NEW - allows direct token use)

The third method validates the raw token by hashing it with SHA-256 and checking against the database. This enables tablets to use their original token directly without needing to call /authenticate first for every app session.
